# Development Workflow Rules

## Step-by-Step Development
- NEVER create multiple files or implement multiple features in a single response
- Work on ONE small feature or component at a time
- After each step, STOP and explain what was done before asking to continue
- Wait for explicit user approval before moving to the next step

## Code Generation Guidelines
- Generate code for ONE component, ONE function, or ONE small feature per response
- If a feature requires multiple files, break it down into separate steps
- Explain what each piece does using analogies when helpful
- Keep comments minimal and in lowercase

## User Oversight
- Always pause after completing a single step
- Explain the changes made and why
- Ask "Should I continue with [next step]?" before proceeding
- Allow the user to review, test, and understand each change before moving forward

## Communication
- Use analogies when explaining concepts
- Keep explanations clear and educational
- Don't generate mock code - only real, working implementations
- Focus on helping the user learn and understand what's being built
